[1840] Ms.A.1.2.9.74

To WLG. [London]. Sends a copy of an article on the American
Abolitionists, which is to be printed in the {u}Eclectic Review{/u}. ...
Says that the doctrines of Non-Resistance “are very imperfectly
understood in this country ...” Outlines the principles of the English
peace advocates. The BFASS “refused even to hear a letter addressed to
them on the subject of woman’s rights. Suggests that WLG write an
article on N-R for an English periodical.


